EZE-DRYING-A METHOD TO SALVAGE SOAKED BOOKS.     134 VALUABLE OLD BOOKS WERE DAMAGED BY WATER FROM THE HOSES OF THE FIREBRIGADE WHEN A BUILDING USED AS STORAGE FOR THE ERZBISCHOFLICHE DIOZESAN- UNDDOMBIBLIOTHEK AT COLOGNE CAUGHT FIRE. AFTER FREEZING THE BOOKS AT -18 C IN ACOLD-STORAGE HOUSE THEY WERE DRIED IN A RENTED FREEZE-DRYING CHAMBER SOMEMONTHS LATER. THE BOOKS WERE RESTORED WITHOUT ANY DAMAGE, OTHER THAN TO THECOVERS WHICH LOST FORM AND HAD TO BE REBOUND